==== INSTALLATION ====


======== KNOWN ISSUES ========

---- assumed array shapes ----
assumed array shapes are not supported in C or Python and compiler dependent. The file 
PythonWrapper.f95 provides wrapper subroutines that converts arrays from assumed to
explicit shapes.

---- optional return parameters ----
optional return parameters are not supported in C or Python. We either have
to return them always which is memory intensive and not good for speed, or
we need two separate subroutines. Affected routines:

======== WRAPPED AND UNWRAPPED FUNCTIONS ========

= LEGENDRE FUNCTIONS =

ALL WRAPPED

